					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">So the memory in the cart is part of the system, huh? I always thought that the memory in the cart was completely copied into the nes's memory and if the program needed to switch it would grab the code from the cart, so that's what I did with my emulator(this time, grabbing code from the rom file). Seems like that's not gonna work now <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />. Hmmm, I'll have to redesign my memory then.
<br />
<br />But now that I think of it, if that was true then I guess you could just pull the cart from the nes at anytime and not screw anything up(at least games with no mappers). Perhaps I was thinking along the lines of cd-based game where the game doesn't immediately screw up cause you took the CD out cause everything that the game currently needs is in ram.</div>

